Residents are alerted to the road closures that will be taking place in the city on Sunday, 01 March, due to the Durban Ultra Triathlon. Metro Police, Senior Superintendent, Parboo Sewpersad, said that the M4/Northern Freeway (North bound) will be closed from 04.00am to 13.00pm, from Sandile Thusi (Argyle) Road to M41 La Lucia turn off.  The road closures will also include: 1.Masabalala Yengwa Avenue and Isaiah Ntshangase road – entrance to Country Club. “Motorist/road users are urged to use the alternative roads – N2, R102 and North Coast Road and to comply with all police officers instructions, ” said Sewpersad.